text:
The most cherished memories that my mum and i have shared or rather the greatest memories i can ever remembered and was touched was that my mum was a hardworking mother. When we were young, she used to wait by the door when we returned from school, standing next to the window at our room, seeing us walk back footstep by footstep, going to the door to open and welcome us home. She used to do everything for us children with a smile on her face. Well, to think back, I was that tiny little pea brain at that time that thought this was just nothing. 
But as I grow up, I thought of it every day, and I misses every little action and effort she had done for us. She made me feel like I was the best in the entire world. She taught me to read and write, she taught me life lesson, she makes my favourite food when she has the free time, and sometime even if she is tired, she will prepare it for us nonetheless. All in all, she does her best to make the happiest girl. @parisnataliewan @joeywanfreedom @jojolicious_wan 😍❤️😘😍❤️😘

text: I would always describe my mum as a selfless heroine! I have never heard her complain abt being tired while working so hard to fend for the family as the sole breadwinner! She displayed a very fierce side of her but she always gives us many many love in secret. Like she always chided me for coming home late, and always bluffing the time I'll be home. But she will never go to bed before I reach home and when I am home she will ask me if I want to drink anything hot or eat anything she cook for me. She always 'complain/nag' when I ask her to cook a certain dish but I can tell u I will definitely have the dish on my dinner table within the next 2-3 days. She loves gardening and she loves all the flowering plants, she even talks and sings to the plants. Oh man, i always laugh at her when she did that but she always say they do listen. Hahaha! My mum is a fighter and she taught me that I should never give up no matter how hard things were. Thank u mummy! I love you 💕 @vivilover2 @jas._.jas @horizonsunset_ 💕
